What is the difference between an adaptive website and a fully responsive website?

- Responsive websites are fluid and adapt to the size of the scree no matter what device. Adaptive Design uses static layouts that are locked to specific sizing.

Describe what it means to be mobile first vs desktop first.

-It means youre designing a website from the mobile perspective first before the Desktop perspective.

What does font-size: 62.5% in the html tag do for us when using rem units?

- it makes the fonts 62.5% or 10px to 1rem therefore letting you type "rem" instead of percentages or other increments in your font sizing.

How would you describe preprocessing to someone new to CSS?

- I would tell them to think of preprocessing as an extension of CSS that lets it work in a much more complex yet simple manner.

What is your favorite concept in preprocessing? What is the concept that gives you the most trouble?

-my favorite concept in preprocessing is nesting. parametric mixins are pretty confusing but I think more and more im geting the hang of it.